1.3
@newl - Update:
* Updated QT5 -> QT6 framework for better future development

@TuKo - Fixed issues:
* `WaitPort()` with no timeout: a busy client (file transfer, blocking socket) never
   acknowledges `AEM_KillClient` → the master *and* the Tool freeze.
* Use-after-free race: the master `PutMsg()`s to the `replyPort` of a client that has
   already self-terminated (port already `DeleteMsgPort`'d).
* Aliasing: `g_AEServerMessagePort` doubles as the command port, the reply port, and
   the registration port for new clients → the master mistakes an `AEM_NewClient` for
   an ack.
* `PMT_SHUTDOWN_SERVER` sets `g_KeepServerRunning = 0` and short-circuits the
   handshake → orphaned children.
* No `SIGBREAKF_CTRL_C` handling → no safety net.


1.2
  * Server side detects dead connections properly now and removes them
  * Apollo V2 and V4 Board Detection improved and V4-A6000 (UniCorn) added
  * Icon added for V4-A6000 (UniCorn)
  * Makefile and Build script added for compile on ApolloCrossDev
  * GetOSName and GetOSVersion integrated into GetOSNameandVersion
  * ApolloBoot and ApolloOS are now detected correct incl. version
  * Added NAME/K to enable Command-Line setting of Server Name (NAME=My-V4-Name-Here)
  * Added ApolloExplorer.incs Icon file for MacOS (before it was a blankm Icon in Dock)
  * Added 256 pixel icons for high resolution Client display
  * Adjusted termination process to (hopefully) avoid the AEDiscovery thread errors after killing ApolloExplorerSrv
  

